.TH "nfp_cpp_area_alloc_with_name" 9 "nfp_cpp_area_alloc_with_name" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nfp_cpp_area_alloc_with_name \- allocate a new CPP area
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct nfp_cpp_area *" nfp_cpp_area_alloc_with_name
.BI "(struct nfp_cpp *cpp "  ","
.BI "u32 dest "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "unsigned long long address "  ","
.BI "unsigned long size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpp" 12
CPP device handle
.IP "dest" 12
NFP CPP ID
.IP "name" 12
Name of region
.IP "address" 12
Address of region
.IP "size" 12
Size of region
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate and initialize a CPP area structure.  The area must later
be locked down with an 'acquire' before it can be safely accessed.
.SH "NOTE"
\fIaddress\fP and \fIsize\fP must be 32-bit aligned values.
.SH "RETURN"
NFP CPP area handle, or NULL
